## Loom Pattern — Reference Implementation for Kit Contributions

The Loom is the authoritative template for how kit contributions work. Key implementation details:

### Registration flow (`loom.ts` lines 134–213)

```typescript
function registerKitRoles(
  pluginId: string,
  packageName: string,
  kit: Record<string, unknown>,
  home: string,
): void {
  const rawRoles = kit.roles;
  if (typeof rawRoles !== 'object' || rawRoles === null || Array.isArray(rawRoles)) return;

  // Dependency-scoped validation
  const allowedPlugins = new Set<string>([
    pluginId,
    ...((kit.requires as string[] | undefined) ?? []),
    ...((kit.recommends as string[] | undefined) ?? []),
  ]);

  for (const [roleName, rawDef] of Object.entries(...)) {
    const qualifiedName = `${pluginId}.${roleName}`;

    // Guild override check at registration time — skip if guild defines this role
    if (config.roles && config.roles[qualifiedName]) continue;

    // ... validate and register ...
    kitRoles.set(qualifiedName, { permissions: validPermissions, ... });
  }
}
```

### Startup scan pattern (lines 330–354)

```typescript
// Phase 1a: Scan all already-loaded standalone kits.
for (const kit of g.kits()) {
  registerKitRoles(kit.id, kit.packageName, kit.kit, home);
}

// Phase 1b: Scan already-started apparatus for supportKit roles.
for (const app of g.apparatuses()) {
  if (app.apparatus.supportKit) {
    registerKitRoles(app.id, app.packageName, app.apparatus.supportKit, home);
  }
}

// Phase 2: Subscribe to plugin:initialized for apparatus supportKits
// that start after the Loom in the dependency order.
ctx.on('plugin:initialized', (plugin: unknown) => {
  const loaded = plugin as LoadedPlugin;
  if (isLoadedApparatus(loaded) && loaded.apparatus.supportKit) {
    registerKitRoles(loaded.id, loaded.packageName, loaded.apparatus.supportKit, home);
  }
});
```

**Important distinction vs Spider's blockType pattern:** The Loom scans **both** kits (Phase 1a) AND already-started apparatus supportKits (Phase 1b). The Spider's `BlockTypeRegistry` only scans standalone kits before startup, then subscribes to `plugin:initialized` for apparatus supportKits. The Loom's Phase 1b is needed because the Loom has `requires: ['tools']`, meaning the Instrumentarium (and any apparatus before the Loom) has already fired `plugin:initialized` — the Loom would miss their supportKit contributions without an explicit scan. The Spider has `requires: ['stacks', 'clerk', 'fabricator']`, same concern applies.

### Override semantics

```typescript
// Guild override check at registration time — skip if guild defines this role
if (config.roles && config.roles[qualifiedName]) continue;
```

Check happens **at registration time**. Config is read in `start()` and cached. Kit contributions that match a guild-defined key are silently skipped.

### Lookup semantics

```typescript
const roleDef = config.roles?.[request.role] ?? kitRoles.get(request.role);
```

Guild config checked first, kit registry second. Both at read time.

